---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="FAQ · CobolDepot" description="Answers to common CobolDepot questions">
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <ul class="space-y-4">
      <li class="rounded-2xl border border-base-200 bg-base-100 p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">How do deployments work?</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80">
          Every push to <code>main</code> triggers Cloudflare Pages to run <code>npm run build</code> and publish the
          static <code>dist/</code> output. Pull requests receive preview URLs.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-2xl border border-base-200 bg-base-100 p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What file formats are supported?</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80">
          Package metadata is YAML-first. Docs live in Markdown/MDX, transformed via Astro during builds.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-2xl border border-base-200 bg-base-100 p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Can I self-host instead of Cloudflare Pages?</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80">
          Yes—Astro emits static assets. You can deploy them to any CDN or object storage bucket if Cloudflare is not
          available, though Pages remains the recommended path.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
